-- Indian shares edge higher; defensive stocks surge
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Fri Jun 27, 2014 06:08AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, June 27 (Reuters) - Indian shares rose on Friday as defensive stocks such as Sun Pharmaceutical Industries <SUN.NS> and Ranbaxy Laboratories <RANB.NS> jumped on the U.S. regulator's approval for a key drug while IT stocks gained after rival Accenture Plc <ACN.N> reported robust quarterly revenue growth.

Ranbaxy provisionally rose 4.6 percent while its new owner Sun Pharma ended 3.9  percent higher. Among software stocks, Tata Consultancy Services <TCS.NS> provisionally rose 4 percent while Infosys <INFY.NS> ended 1.4 percent higher.